                <h3 class=""><strong>Five Steps to Help You Think Through Public Decision Making:</strong></h3>
                <ul class="custom-bullet">
                    <li class="li-spacer-10">
                        <strong class="text-uppercase">Identify the conflict:</strong>
                        Which values are represented? Which are not? What tensions and trade-offs do you see among these values?
                    </li>
                    <li class="li-spacer-10">
                        <strong class="text-uppercase">Represent the public:</strong>
                        Whose values are represented more, whose values less? Are any values missing?
                    </li>
                    <li class="li-spacer-10">
                        <strong class="text-uppercase">Map a direction:</strong>
                        Where do you want to go? Which values or values should have priority?
                    </li>
                    <li class="li-spacer-10">
                        <strong class="text-uppercase">Seek integrative solutions:</strong>
                        Look beyond domination (winner takes all) and compromise (no one is fully satisfied). Seek solutions that satisfy all of the values involved to the greatest degree possible.
                    </li>
                    <li class="li-spacer-10">
                        <strong class="text-uppercase">Chart a course:</strong>
